List of examples of negative wordplay-like alteringof sayings in lyrics of songs (not as lines of lyrics but as abstract meaning). The first word of the altering is always the same:
- "son of a preacherman" -> "son of a bitch"
- "love is blind" -> "love is only skin deep"
- "the early bird gets the worm" -> "the early bird gets the flu"
- "every cloud has a silver lining" -> "every storm brings chaos"
- "time heals all wounds" -> "time scars all hearts"
- "what goes up must come down" -> "what goes around comes around"
- "if at first you don't succeed, try, try again" -> "if at first you don't succeed, give up and try something else"
- "two wrongs don't make a right" -> "two wrongs just make a bigger mess" 
- "ignorance is bliss" -> "ignorance is dangerous"
- "it's better to have loved and lost than to never have loved at all" -> "it's better to never have loved at all"
- "actions speak louder than words" -> "words speak louder than actions"
- "better late than never" -> "better never than late"
- "money can't buy happiness" -> "money can't buy true love"
- "honesty is the best policy" -> "honesty is the best way to ruin a friendship"
- "what doesn't kill you makes you stronger" -> "what doesn't kill you makes you tired and sore" 
- "good things come to those who wait" -> "good things come to those who take action"
- "the grass is always greener on the other side" -> "the grass is always greener where you water it"
- "birds of a feather flock together" -> "birds of a feather get stuck in the same tree"
- "you reap what you sow" -> "you reap what others around you sow as well"
- "the early bird gets the worm" -> "the early bird gets the worm and food poisoning"
- "life is like a box of chocolates" -> "life is like a box of chocolates, you never know what you're allergic to"
